(1, '♪♫ Sgt. Pepper’s one and only Lonely Hearts Club Band /  It’s getting very near the end!  ♪♫', '2018-01-08 14:56:57', '<p>To this point, everyone delivered they own websites and our last assignment is only in our memories. &nbsp;With the new semester shines up and showing us our new classmates and subjects, it&rsquo;s a good time to look back to your activities and do some self-assessment on things. As this is about Web Authoring, I&rsquo;ll talk about my website, in which there&rsquo;s a couple of things that I regret for, but in general, I&rsquo;m kinda happy with the result.</p>\r\n<p><em>(I had picked up that song before the end of the semester and couldn&rsquo;t finish this post back in that time, so, forgive me fellas!)</em></p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"308\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"beatlebob64:V8G2jB4kHesxlwHMqgU2Fg:Z2E73l27UCNwh\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/b9dd382446869306ac458d9e590b9084/tumblr_o8b749PJ671uqrg2lo1_500.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"500\" height=\"308\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"308\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/Z2E73l27UCNwh\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{&quot;tumblelog&quot;:&quot;beatlebob64&quot;,&quot;postId&quot;:&quot;145461706411&quot;}\">Originally posted by beatlebob64</a></p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>As you read here before, my site was about Paul McCartney. Here are some things that I would do totally different if I had the chance:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>1 - After finishing your wireframe, search and refer all the data that you&rsquo;ll use from other sources:&nbsp;</strong>that, I know, was a big issue for some of our classmates, since it&rsquo;s easy to take some images for instance from Google Images and by the end of the work, during the documentation process, have no idea at all in which website you found that pic or that text. I don&rsquo;t have that problem because of a simple lucky strategy: I used Zotero to save all my research and also get almost all of my images from the same source. The only thing that I would do differently it&rsquo;s that I would definitely create the documentation file alongside with the rest of the project, not in the very end. This is because you would probably forget some things after a while.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"210\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"reenacortez:-Kk5hgZJTSG7m5fvEmFJ9Q:ZLqOas2Jkf_UG\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/3f26d7ee2929cb43fc4a95d9ad17c0a7/tumblr_on3yjfrru31snnbgwo1_500.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"500\" height=\"210\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"210\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/ZLqOas2Jkf_UG\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{&quot;tumblelog&quot;:&quot;reenacortez&quot;,&quot;postId&quot;:&quot;158622803856&quot;}\">Originally posted by reenacortez</a></p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p><strong>2 - Finish your HTML file as soon as possible:&nbsp;</strong>that&rsquo;s a mistake that I think not everyone has, but I did: I finished the head and some part of the content of 2 or 3 pages and started to work on my CSS to &ldquo;see how things would be like&rdquo;. After some do&rsquo;s and don\'ts, I walked back to my HTML to finish the pages and that was a great way to get a lot of errors from the Validator.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"371\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"text-mode:_VKeproNrfhzmDlGcT6CYQ:ZXlWwv2AU-X9K\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/017415218f797c1340bd93c2a5945d22/tumblr_obl3fwunYS1rpiyaso1_500.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"500\" height=\"371\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"371\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/ZXlWwv2AU-X9K\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{&quot;tumblelog&quot;:&quot;text-mode&quot;,&quot;postId&quot;:&quot;148696339028&quot;}\">Originally posted by text-mode</a></p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p><strong>3 - Validate all the time. Seriously!:&nbsp;</strong>I don&rsquo;t even need to mention that the Validator is your best friend, and you can&rsquo;t forget him, not even for a second because&hellip; well, I did. And by the end of the work, I was full of little mistakes that I could avoid if I follow all the instructions. Frustrating.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"220\" data-orig-height=\"263\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"fuckmygifdump:LcgTzSMk6guka1OZftSZLw:ZkNo7f2JcdwWm\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/4e96d04035449c60ef6afac583aaeb2a/tumblr_omgy9dpkqd1w0z3jho1_250.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"220\" height=\"263\" data-orig-width=\"220\" data-orig-height=\"263\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/ZkNo7f2JcdwWm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{&quot;tumblelog&quot;:&quot;fuckmygifdump&quot;,&quot;postId&quot;:&quot;158488045616&quot;}\">Originally posted by fuckmygifdump</a></p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p><strong>4 - Get your CSS done and work immediately in your Media Queries:&nbsp;</strong>this is really stupid, but why not full your CSS with all the nice things that you learned in your course and, only when the final due gets very close, started to work on your media queries? Is it sounds stupid enough? And what if I confess that I wasn&rsquo;t that good in media queries to give me the luxury of leaving them to the last hour? Well&hellip; some of them worked, some of them don&rsquo;t. And I&rsquo;ll review that all over again until I get it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"333\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"movietheatreproblems:XZWM32VNxAN_3Ly3BennFg:ZaR4iu23NkhSv\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/524aa55c2999afad5ff46c3bd816e7be/tumblr_o41zrjoSxT1rc4popo1_500.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"333\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/ZaR4iu23NkhSv\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{&quot;tumblelog&quot;:&quot;movietheatreproblems&quot;,&quot;postId&quot;:&quot;141058291513&quot;}\">Originally posted by movietheatreproblems</a></p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p><strong>5 - JavaScript is not for newbies:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>I bet everybody knows that by this point of our journey, but OMG, that hamburger menu took off some of my nights and dreams. I can&rsquo;t imagine how hard another programming this will gonna be in this new semester, but I&rsquo;m already terrified.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-height=\"331\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"trcreativecoding:TbMtaxpNcN_N0Qt7KX9RNw:Z-vobn2L9m4BT\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/15a9e6caf026c6f1635971e49402e4e8/tumblr_op842pR4v71tb0e0qo1_r1_500.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"500\" height=\"331\" data-orig-height=\"331\" data-orig-width=\"500\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/Z-vobn2L9m4BT\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{&quot;tumblelog&quot;:&quot;trcreativecoding&quot;,&quot;postId&quot;:&quot;160151126749&quot;}\">Originally posted by trcreativecoding</a></p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p><strong>6 - Try to get time to write posts up on the date&nbsp;on this blog:</strong>does<strong>&nbsp;</strong>everybody noticed that I started to write this like almost three weeks ago? For now on, let&rsquo;s try and make this content really be up to date (but I can&rsquo;t promise anything, okay?)&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"500\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"upon-a-rainbow:5wtcKIzU89HvoSjgGA4JCA:Z_Nuqw24QWYPq\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/ea52aaac68e89eedb0c4c33b9098916e/tumblr_o52b6zrrPT1r3ea7vo1_500.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"500\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/Z_Nuqw24QWYPq\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{&quot;tumblelog&quot;:&quot;upon-a-rainbow&quot;,&quot;postId&quot;:&quot;142178657908&quot;}\">Originally posted by upon-a-rainbow</a></p>\r\n</figure>', '2', 'Paul McCartney', 'digital media, music, web authoring'),
(2, '♪♫ Oh please, I bet everybody here is fake happy too… ♪♫', '2018-04-20 12:53:03', '<p>This is the last Paramore song released:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/w8vsuOXZBXc#action=share\" width=\"560\" height=\"314\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Okay Rakky, what this has to do with our daily life and assignments?</p>\r\n<p>As we study in Digital Media and Society, we are living a trivial time in our history as human beings: more and more we are connected with others through our cell phones, our favourite social media, our friends from far away and our ways to feel connected. We connect, we share, we exist. But what is real and what is not?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-height=\"217\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"fakehappys:g4bT1Qle1GTVrGXIwckKrw:Zc0Lwv2S5FM_5\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/b986c16520de8b24e582428b407a900e/tumblr_ozkjjpLUf81rpjzdro3_500.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"500\" height=\"217\" data-orig-height=\"217\" data-orig-width=\"500\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/Zc0Lwv2S5FM_5\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{&quot;tumblelog&quot;:&quot;fakehappys&quot;,&quot;postId&quot;:&quot;167591636869&quot;}\">Originally posted by fakehappys</a></p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>Do you ever have a conversation interrupted because your friend needs to answer another on his or her cell phone? Or experimented the sensation of trying to look at your mobile just to not get bored on a class that you&rsquo;re lost or on a meeting that you&rsquo;re not so engaged? More important than that: do you have a feeling that, sometimes, the life of others through their social media is always brighter and happier than yours? Food on Instagram looks taster than on our plates, travelling is something perfect from those posts and nothing wrong ever happen. Why do we need so much to share and to follow?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-height=\"735\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"thingsthatgatherdust:8nH1uwXyb1u9glsrsIZ4Og:ZI6mHo1iP9qF5\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/3209dc7a475b814029c09c0703edf9bf/tumblr_nmsxupnXQy1tu5ekzo1_500.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"500\" height=\"735\" data-orig-height=\"735\" data-orig-width=\"500\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/ZI6mHo1iP9qF5\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{&quot;tumblelog&quot;:&quot;thingsthatgatherdust&quot;,&quot;postId&quot;:&quot;116386120645&quot;}\">Originally posted by thingsthatgatherdust</a></p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>The answers could be in anywhere.&nbsp; At the same time that we need to show ourselves, obeying our exhibitionism sense, we also need to follow, our voyeurism&nbsp;self is activated there.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This video clip inspires me to think all of that because, as the lyrics also said, everyone has a fake happy face to show. But where&rsquo;s the truth of ourselves?&nbsp;</p>', '5', 'John Lennon', ' fake happy, paramore, social media, digital media and society, web authoring'),
(3, '♪ there is no one in here / but yooour body deeeear! ♫', '2018-03-02 14:56:05', '<p>By the end of the second week of Web Authoring, we are creating our own website! I know it sounds &ldquo;nerdish&rdquo;, but I&rsquo;m really liking. As I mentioned before, that wasn&rsquo;t my first experience with HTML language, so it&rsquo;s being fun and, in the same time, a little bit nostalgic. I think the teenager Rakky would be proud of me.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-height=\"230\" data-orig-width=\"340\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"tkd-lyfe:IXiI2t8T5LiUGxljQA99TQ:Zbgffk1n6tJvp\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/2c15a198b78891010ac870abf8c8b5bd/tumblr_npwfjgzWCt1uuqi9mo1_400.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"340\" height=\"230\" data-orig-height=\"230\" data-orig-width=\"340\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/Zbgffk1n6tJvp\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{&quot;tumblelog&quot;:&quot;tkd-lyfe&quot;,&quot;postId&quot;:&quot;121447988851&quot;}\">Originally posted by tkd-lyfe</a></p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p><em>(And I shouldn&rsquo;t have said that!)</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Code time:&nbsp;</strong>we learn how to create lists (unordered or &lt;ul&gt; and ordered or &lt;ol&gt;), using the &lt;li&gt; to put all the items inside it, how to manage our links inside a page (using &lt;a href&gt; and &lt;/a&gt;, and also how to put images in our sites, using the element &lt;img src&gt;. Of course, everything inside the&nbsp;<strong>&lt;body&gt;</strong>!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In a while, we&rsquo;ll be posting our own creations and then&hellip;<em>I really love English but Brazilian Portuguese has some unique expressions like AI A PORRA VAI FICAR S&Eacute;RIA! and I think this is beautiful!&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-height=\"294\" data-orig-width=\"414\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"rainhagretchen:4o2oTooXDr7j5P9u42PaCQ:ZWPpml2EC_Id0\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/40f1950c4b17b625e180ce218abac8bc/tumblr_og2q2jPVcS1u6n38po1_500.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"414\" height=\"294\" data-orig-height=\"294\" data-orig-width=\"414\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/ZWPpml2EC_Id0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{&quot;tumblelog&quot;:&quot;rainhagretchen&quot;,&quot;postId&quot;:&quot;152688994752&quot;}\">Originally posted by rainhagretchen</a></p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>Ah: before I finished, I need to make it be more interessing for not HTML fans, so I decided to put some music on. I spent all my week with the song I mentioned in this article title in my mind. Do you guys know which band I&rsquo;m talking about?&nbsp;</p>', '4', 'George Harrison', 'HTML, html tags, gretchen, brazilian portuguese, links, lists, images, web authoring, digital media'),
(4, '♪♫ For what it’s worth, I know it’s just a word and words betray…♪♫', '2018-05-07 18:06:43', '<p>Last week we finished our studies in HTML language and started to look through&nbsp;CSS, that coding secret that puts colour, order and style in our web pages. During my exercise&nbsp;coding, I realized that sometimes, if you don&rsquo;t put the right word in the right order and in the right place, your entire code will be wrong&nbsp;<em>(and our friend&nbsp;<a href=\"https://t.umblr.com/redirect?z=https%3A%2F%2Fvalidator.w3.org%2F&amp;t=N2YyNDNjYzM2ZTkxOTg5ZTIwM2Y0MmM0ZjJmNWQzZWY2NzAxOTcxYixuWDdWUWhMRA%3D%3D&amp;b=t%3ATjykh__nqh-_c0KFF-nHVw&amp;p=https%3A%2F%2Frakkywebauthoringblog.tumblr.com%2Fpost%2F166323575683%2Ffor-what-its-worth-i-know-its-just-a-word&amp;m=1\">Validator</a>&nbsp;will look at you as you were a fool!)</em>.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"500\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"sleepy-skywalker:K5Iydn0vFRtDBPBwT96CUA:ZYozRd2P75Hql\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/1dcd244cad8f3c6972e26a6a185dd6f2/tumblr_ouwbscE3mo1tbhzhno1_500.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"500\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/ZYozRd2P75Hql\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{&quot;tumblelog&quot;:&quot;sleepy-skywalker&quot;,&quot;postId&quot;:&quot;164401323311&quot;}\">Originally posted by sleepy-skywalker</a></p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>As my colleague&nbsp;<a href=\"https://courtneysharp.tumblr.com/post/166001359764/2-weeks-in\">Courtney</a>&nbsp;explains before me, there&rsquo;s a way to escape those HTML fails: you need to&nbsp;<strong>close</strong>&nbsp;all your tags,&nbsp;<strong>tab</strong>&nbsp;all your code and&nbsp;<strong>validate</strong>&nbsp;while you&rsquo;re coding. It&rsquo;s impossible to be more clear than that.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>My next post will probably be about some CSS rules, but let&rsquo;s finish it for now.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Before I go, I have no idea about why I did it, but here we go, I&rsquo;ll share something weird with you. I put the word &ldquo;HTML&rdquo; on Spotify search tool and I found out that there&rsquo;s a Spotify Playlist called<strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://t.umblr.com/redirect?z=https%3A%2F%2Fopen.spotify.com%2Fuser%2Fcasyphax%2Fplaylist%2F5zJpPVz0KcfOqqyJ532skC&amp;t=MzRkZDIzYzIyMmM3NGNjZjdkYzFhNjk2MjM0YWMxZTJkZTMxYTBjNSxuWDdWUWhMRA%3D%3D&amp;b=t%3ATjykh__nqh-_c0KFF-nHVw&amp;p=https%3A%2F%2Frakkywebauthoringblog.tumblr.com%2Fpost%2F166323575683%2Ffor-what-its-worth-i-know-its-just-a-word&amp;m=1\">&lt;DOCTYPE html&gt;</a></strong>&nbsp;and I think everyone gets the right of knowing it (click on the link and have fun!)&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-height=\"500\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"bycouleurs:KEW6tCWwyQYJ89lW1Gcwgw:ZoGxSm1_IqQ9t\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/1ecd0de5e73dd9cf4b1b1e5ee17ff9a2/tumblr_nzoopmDBjl1tmr6sro1_500.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"500\" data-orig-width=\"500\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/ZoGxSm1_IqQ9t\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{&quot;tumblelog&quot;:&quot;bycouleurs&quot;,&quot;postId&quot;:&quot;135607198327&quot;}\">Originally posted by bycouleurs</a></p>\r\n</figure>', '6', 'No Author', 'web authoring, media, digital media, miscellaneous'),
(5, '♪♫ Color Matters!  ♪♫', '2017-09-30 14:04:47', '<p>In a brief research about colours, I found this&nbsp;<a href=\"https://t.umblr.com/redirect?z=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.colormatters.com&amp;t=MmIxYjRlZmVkYjY4ZWQyMTIzODQ2NDAyMDNmM2EwZjBiNzM0M2RiMix2VEZQcVFTUw%3D%3D&amp;b=t%3AfynjNBjfpQMPOl_rKyayXw&amp;p=https%3A%2F%2Frakkyvisualcommunicationblog.tumblr.com%2Fpost%2F168181410398%2Fcolor-matters&amp;m=1\">amazing website</a>&nbsp;about colours and their uses in our days, through marketing, brand, advertising and also to express feelings, moods and ways to see the world.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Colour automatically express feelings and ways to see things, but we see the colour before even think about anything else. What if your favourite french&nbsp;fries portions weren&rsquo;t yellow with that red catchup alongside, but instead, blue with a purple catchup? Not very appetizing, right?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"288\" data-orig-height=\"240\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"x--hydrangea:lgcxB39NJoeMUZQnQhan3w:ZCYYmn2GgyeF3\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/48540cdb99546d875bdff457db14aa63/tumblr_oj78g1g6We1tzpqexo1_400.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"288\" height=\"240\" data-orig-width=\"288\" data-orig-height=\"240\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/ZCYYmn2GgyeF3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{\">Originally posted by x--hydrangea</a></p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>I like to express myself with neutral colours, like black, white, calm tons of blues and grey, nothing so colourful or none of the extravaganza style. Sometimes, I think that in that way I can spread an image of myself as a calm and happy person that used to do things in a discreet way.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"400\" data-orig-height=\"240\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"watersslut:hHnNjS3N-d-_rDyd1nZTHA:ZR7Xjs1g7DK7V\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/62c56993084d8a851decf11106d64ab0/tumblr_nle68sXJFb1s8ir5qo1_400.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"400\" height=\"240\" data-orig-width=\"400\" data-orig-height=\"240\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/ZR7Xjs1g7DK7V\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{\">Originally posted by watersslut</a></p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>What about you? Which colour do you think that represents your fully self? Which one is your favourite colour?</p>', '5', 'Ringo Starr', 'color, pallete, the beatles, yellow submarine, color wheel'),
(6, '♪♫ Helvetica everywhere! ♪♫', '2018-04-18 14:06:29', '<p>Do you guys remember that Hurricane Holiday?</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/f356f7159a8771f7dbd8d445104dad3c/tumblr_inline_p058971jdZ1v8k7vx_1280.jpg\" alt=\"image\" width=\"700\" height=\"1120\" data-orig-width=\"900\" data-orig-height=\"1440\" /></p>\r\n<p>Yeah, back in that Monday, I followed Tara&rsquo;s recommendation and watched Helvetica, the movie&nbsp;<span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">(</span><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">such a nerd, I&nbsp;</span><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">know!</span>). Since then, by the way, I&rsquo;m the Helvetica personification of this gif:</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"272\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"houseofhorrorx:ORKHn1oZmqTD374Sd-bj2w:ZcXWVh24ba7-z\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/69372be38a28c071010b5366d2ecb04e/tumblr_o589okqqLY1vpka12o1_500.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"500\" height=\"272\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"272\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/ZcXWVh24ba7-z\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{\">Originally posted by houseofhorrorx</a></p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>- I see Helvetica type.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>- How often do you see them?&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>- All the time!&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p>And I mean it:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"615\" data-orig-height=\"164\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/64ff7f088d0f06ae8530b6a6061d0cb1/tumblr_inline_p057us02NH1v8k7vx_1280.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"615\" height=\"164\" data-orig-width=\"615\" data-orig-height=\"164\" /></figure>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"615\" data-orig-height=\"272\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/7ba2636c5361b26737982dca127df01d/tumblr_inline_p057utVur31v8k7vx_1280.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"615\" height=\"272\" data-orig-width=\"615\" data-orig-height=\"272\" /></figure>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"550\" data-orig-height=\"552\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/473b9b6d8c6e49247f36fc8a2a5e4dad/tumblr_inline_p057uxxLLW1v8k7vx_1280.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"550\" height=\"552\" data-orig-width=\"550\" data-orig-height=\"552\" /></figure>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"2448\" data-orig-height=\"3264\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/eac32cbb946954165ea806810d5ac100/tumblr_inline_p057v0PcTo1v8k7vx_1280.jpg\" alt=\"image\" width=\"700\" height=\"933\" data-orig-width=\"2448\" data-orig-height=\"3264\" /></figure>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"3264\" data-orig-height=\"2448\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/ae4cd8d428852b4fafc3f64804d3d4a8/tumblr_inline_p057v3dTUz1v8k7vx_1280.jpg\" alt=\"image\" width=\"700\" height=\"525\" data-orig-width=\"3264\" data-orig-height=\"2448\" /></figure>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"2453\" data-orig-height=\"1707\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/3108f47b87bb5ec3281eeb1c1384916b/tumblr_inline_p057v70Owb1v8k7vx_1280.jpg\" alt=\"image\" width=\"700\" height=\"487\" data-orig-width=\"2453\" data-orig-height=\"1707\" /></figure>\r\n<p><em>(This is Arial, my mistake!)</em></p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"3264\" data-orig-height=\"2448\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/fa933484312e7d08af56fa9e18ad2d86/tumblr_inline_p057vchgWV1v8k7vx_1280.jpg\" alt=\"image\" width=\"700\" height=\"525\" data-orig-width=\"3264\" data-orig-height=\"2448\" /></figure>\r\n<p>Helvetica, the documentary, tells the story of Helvetica, the font that can express everything, the most famous typeface in the world, and how it becomes so popular and so meaningful. And seriously, after watching it, it&rsquo;s impossible to not see Helvetica. I also started to use Helvetica in all of my assignments cause, OMG, it&rsquo;s an amazingly simple beautiful font!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To summarize, it&rsquo;s an interesting movie. Watch it!</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-embed tmblr-full\"></figure>', '6', 'Rakky Curvelo', 'helvetica, typefaces, '),
(7, '♪♫ Fail miserably… an unnecessary explanation! ♪♫', '2017-12-26 15:09:57', '<p>As you already realised (everyone that reads this blog), I fail miserably in detail my step by step to the production of my Music Poster, and as you, Applied Digital Media students already know,&nbsp;it was because of the other assignments deadlines coming closer and closer and making us really feel the pressure.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>That said, I just think that would be fair if I publish my final result here, as a public apology for a promise that I didn&rsquo;t keep.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"1240\" data-orig-height=\"1616\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/a8451e2f4f26ae6a6df5a13d0a4b958a/tumblr_inline_p055k9IrXt1v8k7vx_1280.jpg\" alt=\"image\" width=\"700\" height=\"912\" data-orig-width=\"1240\" data-orig-height=\"1616\" /></figure>\r\n<p>Is it cool, right? At the end of the day, I like it! =)&nbsp;</p>', '5', 'Rakky Curvelo', 'Digital Media, Visual Communication'),
(8, '♪♫ My music poster - 1st impressions to the Earth! ♪♫', '2018-02-20 15:26:47', '<p>Stoner rock.&nbsp;Far From Alaska. That was my first idea about the music poster that I&rsquo;d like to create to our Visual Communication assignment N&ordm; 1. It will be easy: they are on the top of the best music bands in my country, already receive international awards and just release a great new album:&nbsp;<strong>Unlikely</strong>&nbsp;(seriously, you&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://t.umblr.com/redirect?z=https%3A%2F%2Fopen.spotify.com%2Fartist%2F1ztNPX8z169arfAY0TWFLB&amp;t=Yjg3NjcwMzI4ZGY2ZDY3YmZhMDAyZGQyMjZiZDRlMDdkNmU4OGExZCwwcWtFSkREWQ%3D%3D&amp;b=t%3AfynjNBjfpQMPOl_rKyayXw&amp;p=https%3A%2F%2Frakkyvisualcommunicationblog.tumblr.com%2Fpost%2F166688566718%2Fmusic-poster&amp;m=1\">NEED TO LISTEN TO THIS GUYS</a></strong>!).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"309\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/e22da173383292d8ddc3668f983c1d05/tumblr_inline_oxjwmo4EaW1v8k7vx_500.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"500\" height=\"309\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"309\" /></figure>\r\n<p>But then I changed my mind&hellip; how could I possible represented something with so many colours and shapes without creating something similar on with they already have in their posters and advertisements? How could I be inventive and in the same time create something really cool about they, present all the feelings that they made me feel when I listen to their music? (Don&rsquo;t worry. Far From Alaska is a band that always will be in my heart and that you will be hearing about them soon,&nbsp;<em>maybe in another assignment</em>).</p>\r\n<p>Then I remember the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://t.umblr.com/redirect?z=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.allmusic.com%2Falbum%2Fclube-da-esquina-mw0000627685&amp;t=NzdlNWNiZTNjNDNmOWQwOTk2NDYxOGMwYzZiYmI0NDhmZTRkMDI2YiwwcWtFSkREWQ%3D%3D&amp;b=t%3AfynjNBjfpQMPOl_rKyayXw&amp;p=https%3A%2F%2Frakkyvisualcommunicationblog.tumblr.com%2Fpost%2F166688566718%2Fmusic-poster&amp;m=1\">Clube da Esquina</a>&nbsp;songs. They&rsquo;re a progressive rock band back in the 70&prime;s that is not together anymore, but I always like the music they made. One of my dreams were seen they playing along, but that&rsquo;s not possible - some of the guys are already dead, others are producing different music and I had a lucky day when I saw&nbsp;<strong>Milton Nascimento</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>Lo Borges</strong>&nbsp;together,&nbsp;<em>but this is a topic for another post.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"640\" data-orig-height=\"426\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/af476173f1122a71195f6d15987bc2ea/tumblr_inline_oy8xglo6n41v8k7vx_1280.jpg\" alt=\"image\" width=\"640\" height=\"426\" data-orig-width=\"640\" data-orig-height=\"426\" /></figure>\r\n<p>Within these ideas&nbsp;in my mind, I decided that I will create a dreaming poster with a couple of concerts of them here in Dublin. And I&rsquo;ll represent their imaginative way to put their music together using shapes as squares and lines, and a lot of psychedelic colours.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For starts, I think about the Font. Some of my ideas are using&nbsp;<a href=\"https://t.umblr.com/redirect?z=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fontsquirrel.com%2Ffonts%2FDiner-Skinny%3Fq%255Bterm%255D%3Dretro%26q%255Bsearch_check%255D%3DY&amp;t=OGE2NzhkYWNhNmZmNzhmMWM2NWRkYjk1M2Y0OTMyZTUyY2JhODVlNSwwcWtFSkREWQ%3D%3D&amp;b=t%3AfynjNBjfpQMPOl_rKyayXw&amp;p=https%3A%2F%2Frakkyvisualcommunicationblog.tumblr.com%2Fpost%2F166688566718%2Fmusic-poster&amp;m=1\">Diner Skinny</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://t.umblr.com/redirect?z=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fontsquirrel.com%2Ffonts%2FPricedown%3Fq%255Bterm%255D%3Dretro%26q%255Bsearch_check%255D%3DY&amp;t=MTJkODFkNGRlYTU4YTZjOGY0OGQ1NDZmMTkxMGRiZTRlMThmOTg1NiwwcWtFSkREWQ%3D%3D&amp;b=t%3AfynjNBjfpQMPOl_rKyayXw&amp;p=https%3A%2F%2Frakkyvisualcommunicationblog.tumblr.com%2Fpost%2F166688566718%2Fmusic-poster&amp;m=1\">Pricedown</a>&nbsp;(a natural winner). I&rsquo;m still looking for the colours, but I&rsquo;ll definitely start putting some yellow and blue scale on it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This sounds like a thing that it takes time and some effort. So, I&rsquo;ll put it on a series of posts, and leave you now, with one of my favourite song of them. Enjoy!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-embed tmblr-full\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/8U3-cC7BMg8?feature=oembed&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https://safe.txmblr.com&amp;wmode=opaque\" width=\"700\" height=\"525\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" data-mce-fragment=\"1\"></iframe></figure>', '1', 'Paul McCartney', 'Ireland, Paul McCartney, Clube da Esquina, Visual Communication'),
(9, '♪♫ As you were, LG! ', '2018-04-22 14:15:49', '<p>I know this is not a complex piece of an advertisement or what we can say that&rsquo;s inspiring for those that walk through this on their ways to the job or school, but guys, let&rsquo;s face it:&nbsp;<strong><em>LIAM GALLAGHER IS COMING!&nbsp;</em></strong></p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"960\" data-orig-height=\"1280\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/f3c4628a2dcdfcca8cf3cbb04f86ba88/tumblr_inline_oxpg4qGkqc1v8k7vx_1280.jpg\" alt=\"image\" width=\"700\" height=\"933\" data-orig-width=\"960\" data-orig-height=\"1280\" /></figure>\r\n<p>You have no idea who is this guy? 90&rsquo;s, Britpop, the huge battle between&nbsp;<strong>Oasis&nbsp;</strong>and&nbsp;<strong>Blur</strong>&nbsp;and then the final fight of Gallagher&rsquo;s brothers finishing their band and broken all of the fans hearts&hellip; Well, I&rsquo;ve been there all the time and<em>&nbsp;I STILL GOT NO TICKETS FOR THIS CONCERT YET</em>, so if anyone knows anyone that can help me, PLEAAASSEEEE!!!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"307\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"slaughteringbunnies:Lcu-m2Gj4xFC235lOjgdgQ:ZgzG3q2MjJwkr\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/78f2a241ff9f1a4baf8a68bf98b47bbd/tumblr_oripv03FpO1smsmqro1_500.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"500\" height=\"307\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-orig-height=\"307\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/ZgzG3q2MjJwkr\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{&quot;tumblelog&quot;:&quot;slaughteringbunnies&quot;,&quot;postId&quot;:&quot;161821469621&quot;}\">Originally posted by slaughteringbunnies</a></p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>Okay, coming back to the visual stuff, this is a very simple poster which presents the cover of the<strong>&nbsp;Liam Gallagher</strong>&nbsp;first solo album and his face over it. When you listen to the album (yeah, I&rsquo;m doing it again&nbsp;<a href=\"https://t.umblr.com/redirect?z=https%3A%2F%2Fopen.spotify.com%2Falbum%2F2V3WS9tlPYmscBNWHHYu9X&amp;t=NTFkYzRmY2FmM2Y2NWY2YjM0ZjY1N2M0MDI1M2ZlYWMzOTYzZmVlMSxKeU1nRmFQdw%3D%3D&amp;b=t%3AfynjNBjfpQMPOl_rKyayXw&amp;p=https%3A%2F%2Frakkyvisualcommunicationblog.tumblr.com%2Fpost%2F166319527248%2Fliam-g&amp;m=1\">right now</a>) you find out that those songs could be been&nbsp;on an&nbsp;<strong>Oasis</strong>&nbsp;record, but also presents a lot of the personality of&nbsp;<strong>Liam Gallagher&nbsp;</strong>himself. The name of the record for instance,&nbsp;<strong>&ldquo;As You Were&rdquo;</strong>, has been his signature on almost every single tweet, since I can recall (<a href=\"https://twitter.com/liamgallagher/status/760561287839510529\">and</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/liamgallagher/status/809804216311103488\">here</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/liamgallagher/status/694548579420094464\">you</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/liamgallagher/status/856251562011873284\">can see&nbsp;</a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/liamgallagher/status/733717823697096705\">some proof</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/liamgallagher/status/748899251258793985\">of it!</a>).</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"400\" data-orig-height=\"202\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"oasis--beadyeye:1N_qmgfn2_GWsEDhEXCUbg:ZraXMj2FHj7UE\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/d41c01e90765d856329db950cb173662/tumblr_ohfm2ncWIK1uhpkqmo1_400.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"400\" height=\"202\" data-orig-width=\"400\" data-orig-height=\"202\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/ZraXMj2FHj7UE\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{&quot;tumblelog&quot;:&quot;oasis--beadyeye&quot;,&quot;postId&quot;:&quot;153842120590&quot;}\">Originally posted by oasis--beadyeye</a></p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>All those silly things connected could make this simple advertisement look different now. Maybe you&rsquo;re thinking about how they create this connection with what&nbsp;<strong>Liam</strong>&nbsp;wants to say, in this simple graphic representation of his name, with black and beige colours and some simple typography. For me, this is what I want to do with my Visual Communication pieces: something that makes people think.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For now, let me only finishing this post with a&nbsp;<strong>Liam Gallagher</strong>message for all of us, living in Dublin right now (and sorry for the quality of the picture!):&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-width=\"960\" data-orig-height=\"1280\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/8214333bced0248cb30180656c3b1a64/tumblr_inline_oxpg4qnbLL1v8k7vx_1280.jpg\" alt=\"image\" width=\"700\" height=\"933\" data-orig-width=\"960\" data-orig-height=\"1280\" /></figure>', '4', 'Paul McCartney', 'Liam Gallagher, Dublin, Visual Communication'),
(10, '♪♫ Broadcast the boom boom boom boom / And make ‘em all dance to it ♪♫', '2018-04-03 14:16:49', '<p>My first post of 2018 it will be about my podcast - and I&rsquo;m late on sharing this, right? - but, well, let&rsquo;s do it now.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-height=\"296\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"elibangbang:f0INIRAph7A5yYyJbImiAQ:ZhNATu2585WNq\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/360ac6d3d5dc75ff0d0af51129210702/tumblr_o5rvrfpqyz1ret3z9o1_500.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"500\" height=\"296\" data-orig-height=\"296\" data-orig-width=\"500\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/ZhNATu2585WNq\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{&quot;tumblelog&quot;:&quot;elibangbang&quot;,&quot;postId&quot;:&quot;142943323636&quot;}\">Originally posted by elibangbang</a></p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>I used this opportunity to talk about the way in which people discover music through the web and the relationship between musicians and independent music websites. To help me out, I interviewed my friend and editor of the music website&nbsp;<a href=\"https://t.umblr.com/redirect?z=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.tenhomaisdiscosqueamigos.com%2F&amp;t=YjBiMDFhM2ZlNDhmMjQzNWFkOWYwMDBkYmY5ZmFhNzA2MzEwNjliNCxRdFlydjZnSg%3D%3D&amp;b=t%3ATjykh__nqh-_c0KFF-nHVw&amp;p=https%3A%2F%2Frakkywebauthoringblog.tumblr.com%2Fpost%2F169768022238%2Fbroadcast-the-boom-boom-boom-boom-and-make&amp;m=1\">Tenho Mais Discos Que Amigos</a>&nbsp;(I Have More Records Than Friends)&nbsp;<a href=\"https://t.umblr.com/redirect?z=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.tenhomaisdiscosqueamigos.com%2Fauthor%2Fadmin%2F&amp;t=NjMzMmQyODA3YmRhYzllMTg3OTYwODAyOTNlZjQxMTQ5ZWJkM2RhMCxRdFlydjZnSg%3D%3D&amp;b=t%3ATjykh__nqh-_c0KFF-nHVw&amp;p=https%3A%2F%2Frakkywebauthoringblog.tumblr.com%2Fpost%2F169768022238%2Fbroadcast-the-boom-boom-boom-boom-and-make&amp;m=1\">Tony Aiex</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://t.umblr.com/redirect?z=https%3A%2F%2Fsoundcloud.com%2Frakky-curvelo%2Fraquelline-curvelo-2957739-web-authoring-podcast&amp;t=M2FkMjQyZWNlYjdmYjQyMTk4MTE5NjAwM2ViOWMwMTIyMGVlMmJiOSxRdFlydjZnSg%3D%3D&amp;b=t%3ATjykh__nqh-_c0KFF-nHVw&amp;p=https%3A%2F%2Frakkywebauthoringblog.tumblr.com%2Fpost%2F169768022238%2Fbroadcast-the-boom-boom-boom-boom-and-make&amp;m=1\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/5f9f7757a19da3d5f881ff764fbae7bb/tumblr_inline_p2n75mnZrx1v8k7vx_540.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>As our best record from 2017 was Melodrama, by Lorde (if you want to check the list,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://t.umblr.com/redirect?z=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.tenhomaisdiscosqueamigos.com%2F2017%2F12%2F04%2Fmelhores-discos-internacionais-2017%2F&amp;t=MmQ0YmEwMzBkNjA1ZDJmNTZmNTBiN2UzMjg3ZmFlNzc5ZmI2YjRhMyxRdFlydjZnSg%3D%3D&amp;b=t%3ATjykh__nqh-_c0KFF-nHVw&amp;p=https%3A%2F%2Frakkywebauthoringblog.tumblr.com%2Fpost%2F169768022238%2Fbroadcast-the-boom-boom-boom-boom-and-make&amp;m=1\">click here</a>) I can&rsquo;t avoid it. This post needs to have Lorde on it!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-height=\"281\" data-orig-width=\"500\" data-tumblr-attribution=\"believeinyouridols:GVusHR_qEMvDMYUds8_6pA:ZxHHxs24Pzecw\"><img src=\"https://78.media.tumblr.com/9ef875ae4d91f71d64c4df7e55f88612/tumblr_o51xixY6nT1s6d4r9o1_500.gif\" alt=\"image\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" data-orig-height=\"281\" data-orig-width=\"500\" />\r\n<p class=\"tmblr-attribution\"><a href=\"https://tmblr.co/ZxHHxs24Pzecw\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-peepr=\"{&quot;tumblelog&quot;:&quot;believeinyouridols&quot;,&quot;postId&quot;:&quot;142169508282&quot;}\">Originally posted by believeinyouridols</a></p>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>I hope you enjoy it!</p>', '5', 'Rakky Curvelo', 'Lorde, podcast, Digital Media');

